iate space, find place, and transform identity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 0aGender identityxPhilosophy. 4aGender and Sexuality : Gender Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women in Religion. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Feminist Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Metaphysics.2bisacsh1 aCrapo Kim, Ruthanne, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRussell, Yvette, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSharp, Brenda, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848847940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438488479423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438488479/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles